{"type":"message","id":"35c2a443","parentId":"24770a24","timestamp":"2026-03-20T19:55:59.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting repository structure**\n\nI'm considering how to check the top level of a repository, starting with a standard read. I noticed that we don't have raw outputs due to truncation. Using exec could be a way to list files more concisely, but I need to know what project files are present. I'll inspect them using the find command to get a comprehensive picture of what's in the repository. Let’s see what I can uncover!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4hO1X7rFWFPmwNHDiLmb9lGn","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"printf 'ROOT\\n'; find . -maxdepth 2 -type f | sed 's#^./##' | sort | grep -E '(^package.json$|^pnpm-workspace.yaml$|^tsconfig.json$|^src/|^app/|^pages/|^game/|^openclaw.json$|^README|^vite|^cocos|^miniprogram|^project.config.json|^game.config.json)' | head -200","workdir":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace","timeout":20,"security":"allowlist"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":101651,"output":966,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102617,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774036549726}}
